{
  "text": "Our study had several key strengths, including the 2 ϫ 2 factorial design and the use of active control conditions, which enabled us to control for factors such as social interaction during the group exercise class and mental stimulation associated with using a computer. However, there is growing evidence that even these less intensive interventions may have cognitive and physical benefits in older adults. [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] Future studies should consider inclusion of both active and no-contact control conditions.",
  "correct_citation": {
